<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1910-06-17T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1910-06-17T00:00:00-05:00" n="519" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d519">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Ambassador <persName type="from">Dudley</persName>
                                to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Petropolis</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1910-06-17"><hi rend="italic">June 17,
                                1910</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Your June 15, repeated from Buenos Aires. Brazilian minister for foreign
                            affairs says he will telegraph Brazilian legations Lima and Quito to
                            present similar notes respecting further withdrawal of troops and
                            demobilization.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Dudley.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>